    <example xml:id="auto_nyx3xjow">
        <statement>
            <p xml:id="auto_eyjiijcq">
                Nonagon example.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_x27hly33">
                One of the angles of a regular polygon is <m>40^\circ</m> and its sides are <m>15 \text{cm}</m> long. Sketch the polygon and
                then find the area of the polygon.
            </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
            <p xml:id="auto_95uoxdph">
                
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_i9xh0joa">
                ðŸ”¹ From the definition of a polygon all interior angle add up to <m>360^ \circ</m>.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_3g04mn5z">
               ðŸ”¹ To find the number of sides of a triangle we use the formula <m>\frac{360}{\text{Interior angle}} = \text{Number of sides}</m>. </p> 
               <p xml:id="auto_h6h2ly5b">
                
               Where <m>n</m> is the number of sides.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_4gtjcv8e"> <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{360^ \circ}{\text{interior angle}} = \amp \text{ Number of sides} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \frac{360^\circ}{40} = \amp 9 \text{ sides }</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_ykagz334">
                ðŸ”¹Finding the area of the nonagon we use the formula:
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_hdzukn7q">
                Area of a tringle using sine rule <m>\times \text{the number of sides} </m> Where our <m>ab </m> is the radii.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_rmhzj7vw">
                <md>
                    <mrow> \frac{1}{2}ab \, \text{sin} 40^\circ  = \amp \frac {1}{2} \times 15\text{cm} \times 15\text{cm} \times  \text{sin} \, 40^\circ  </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp \frac{1}{2} \times 225 \times 0.6428 \text{ cm}^2 </mrow>
                </md> 
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_fgcoqzug">
               ðŸ”¹ There are 9 triangles since a nonagon has 9 sides.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_32vh1916">
                ðŸ”¹Therefore, total area is:
            </p>
            <p xml:id="auto_0jtssbjb">
                <md>
                    <mrow>  = \amp 9 \times  (\frac{1}{2} \times 225 \times 0.6428 ) </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp 9 \times 225 \times 0.3214 </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp 73.6006 \text{ cm}^2</mrow>
                </md>
            </p>
        </solution>
    </example>
    
